{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a35be96a-e447-4ecb-bd99-31d0f6e1b60f","content":"The workflow is ready. Here's the full setup:\n\n---\n\n### GitHub Actions Workflow (✅ created)\n`.github/workflows/publish.yml` — triggers on `v*` tags. Key elements:\n- **`id-token: write`** — lets GitHub issue an OIDC token to the workflow\n- **`--api-key az`** — placeholder value; NuGet authenticates via the OIDC token, not a real API key\n\n### nuget.org Configuration (manual step)\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n   *(If the package doesn't exist yet, go to your account settings → Trusted Publishers)*\n2. **Add Trusted Publisher** with:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank unless you add a GitHub environment)*\n\n### Publishing\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\n> **Tip:** If you want deployment protection (approval gates), add an `environment: nuget` to the workflow job and specify that environment name in the nuget.org trusted publisher config too.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b3e1d263-a5a7-411d-adf6-e51f08484a1b","outputTokens":295,"requestId":"1C13:1DC1AD:5F26C35:669D0A3:69FBE374"},"id":"857ce877-748d-4184-8b3e-345449cd930a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:37.127Z","parentId":"72b64383-c3c9-4cf9-bb37-1d38fa8ba20e"}
